## OML4Py  Data Cleaning: Outlier Removal
In this notebook, we demonstrate how to exclude records with outliers using OML4Py. 

We use the customer insurance lifetime value data set which contains customer financial information, lifetime value, and whether or not the customer bought insurance.

In the dataset CUSTOMER_INSURANCE_LTV, we focus on numerical values and remove the records with values in the top and bottom 5%.

paragraphs.title: Get the 5 and 95 percentile
paragraphs.text:
%python

df = CUST_DF['INCOME'].describe(percentiles = [0.05,0.95])
df = pd.DataFrame(df)
df = df.reset_index()

lower = df[df['index'] == '5%']['INCOME'].values[0]
upper = df[df['index'] == '95%']['INCOME'].values[0]

print("Lower: ", lower)
print("Upper: ", upper)

paragraphs.title: Remove data with INCOME above 95% level
Plot the distribution before outlier removal using OML  graphics
paragraphs.text:
%python

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
plt.style.use('seaborn')

plt.figure(figsize=[20,6])
oml.graphics.hist(CUST_DF['INCOME'], bins=10, color='C0',
                 linestyle='solid', edgecolor='black')

plt.title('Histogram of INCOME before outlier removeal')
plt.xlabel('INCOME')
plt.ylabel('Customer Counts')
_ = plt.show()
